  "text": "In 1981, Penchansky and Thomas 6 identified the importance of access as a key concept in health policy and health policy research, proposing a model with five key dimensions of access (Box 1). More recently, Fortney and colleagues [CITATION_1] have identified the need to recognise a 'digital dimension' to access, incorporating the potential for synchronous and asynchronous virtual interactions with the evolving healthcare system.",
  "correct_citation": {
